STATEMENT IN SUPPORT OF APPLICATION FOR VETERAN READINESS AND EMPLOYMENT (VA Form 28-1900)

Veteran: [Your Name]
VA Claim Number: [Your Claim Number]
Date: {{date}}

Section I: Basic Eligibility & Case Stage
- Current Case Stage: {{stage}}
- Military Discharge Character: {{discharge}}
- Service-Connected Disability Rating: {{rating}}%
- Active Duty / IDES Status: {{activeDutyIDES}}

Section II: Statement of Employment Handicap (38 C.F.R. § 21.51)
Under 38 C.F.R. § 21.51, an Employment Handicap exists when a veteran has a vocational impairment caused in substantial part by the contribution of service-connected disabilities, which has not yet been overcome.

My service-connected conditions directly interfere with my ability to obtain or maintain suitable employment because:
{{employmentBarriers}}

I have experienced the following vocational impairments (unemployment, underemployment, or medical issues at work):
{{vocationalImpairments}}

Section III: Serious Employment Handicap Factors (38 C.F.R. § 21.52) [If Applicable]
{{sehJustification}}

Section IV: Vocational Feasibility Statement (38 C.F.R. § 21.53)
{{feasibilityStatement}}

Section V: Proposed Rehabilitation Goal
My proposed vocational goal is {{proposedGoal}}. This career field is compatible with my physical and cognitive limitations because:
{{goalCompatibility}}

Request for Assessment:
I request a formal evaluation for Chapter 31 services. I assert that my facts satisfy the criteria for basic eligibility and entitlement. If a vocational goal is deemed not feasible, I request a referral for an Extended Evaluation (38 C.F.R. § 21.74) or Independent Living services (38 C.F.R. § 21.76).

Sincerely,

[Your Name]
